⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Mana
node MTG · MTG · ⟦Mana:MTG:259baa⟧

WHO   — Mana — the resource · the land
WHAT  — The economy of the game: tap lands for mana, climb the ‘curve,’ and balance the agony of too few or too many lands (‘mana screw’ and ‘flood’).
WHERE — MTG · MTG Arena  Framework inputs: Magic: The Gathering / MTG Arena (WotC)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Magic's central tension is resources over time — the land you draw decides the game as much as the spells.
HOW   — By lands tapped for coloured mana, a curve of costs, and the eternal gamble of the mana base.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the land turned to power — too little of me and you're screwed, too much and you flood; the whole game balances on me.

spoken token : mol-mik-raend   ·   hex : 259baa
